11-17 update!

I have now processed the CS Time Conflict Override form for the first time. If I was able to move you into the class, I did so.

There were MANY people who didn't meet the reserve cap requirements & so I was unable to enroll you. Also, most upper division classes are at capacity until we release more seats once GSIs are hired so I was unable to process those time conflicts.

DO NOT EMAIL ME IF YOU FILLED OUT THE CONFLICT FORM BUT DIDN'T GET INTO THE CLASS! There are just too many of you for me to respond to. DO THIS INSTEAD:  Keep filling out the time conflict form if you are still interested in the class. I process the form every 3 business days. The next time I process it will be next Wednesday - 11/22.  [see original posting with link below]

Regards,

Cindy Conners

=======Original Post===========

We will continue to override time conflicts for students for this spring.

 

The enrollment system does not allow you to enroll directly in classes that have time conflicts. This must be processed by the SIS team (instructions). If you have filled out the SIS form, but your request has still not been processed after 36 hours, we will override CS class conflicts for you via a Google form (links below), space permitting.

Please note that by filling out the form(s), you agree to have a class conflict overridden for you. It is your responsibility to check the attendance policies and make plans for conflicting exams.

 

Please do not contact us after filling out the form to check on the status of your request. Beginning in Phase 2, we will process the form every 3 business days.

 

Use the CS Time Conflict Override form, if you're trying to enroll in an COMPSCI class.

(There is a different form for EE and EECS class time conflict. See the appropriate pinned post for that form.)

 

You must meet the enrollment priorities (if any) when you fill out the form in order to be enrolled. There must be space open in your category in order for you to be enrolled.

 

**Please make sure you have checked your enrolled and waitlisted units. Phase I maximum is 13.5, Phase II is 17.5, and the Adjustment Period is 20.5. We cannot override the maximum units for you and this causes a delay in processing requests.**
